BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260430T233000Z
DTEND:20260501T003000Z
DTSTAMP:20260430T000000Z
SUMMARY:Poetry Open Mic Night
DESCRIPTION:Calling all poets and poetry lovers!\n\nJoin us for an 
 inclusive and welcoming evening of poems led by featured poets\, Charles 
 Kiley and Danielle Pitter.\n\nStep up to the mic and share your own writing 
 or a work by one of your favorites.\n\nAbout our featured poets \n♦ 
 Charles Kiley has an MFA in poetry from Drew University. His work has been 
 featured on Every Day Poets and Every Day Fiction.  \n♦ Danielle Pitter 
 is an author\, poet\, and librarian from Woodbridge\, NJ. Her two poetry 
 books\, Reality Check and Destinations\, are available on Amazon and Barnes 
 & Noble. Visit her website PoetryBooksYA for more book-related content. 
 \n\nYou may also know them both from their additional roles as part of the 
 West Orange Public Library staff.    \n\nThis program is geared towards 
 adults.\nWe will also be hosting a Teen Poetry Open Mic on Saturday\, April 
 18.
LOCATION:West Orange - Community Room 1\, West Orange Public Library
ORGANIZER;CN="West Orange Library":MAILTO:events@westorange.bccls.org
CATEGORIES:Author Event/Talk
UID:LibCal-10341-16581071
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/16581071
END:VEVENT
