BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260513T223000Z
DTEND:20260514T003000Z
DTSTAMP:20260513T000000Z
SUMMARY:Abstract Collage Class
DESCRIPTION:A 3-session art class for adults with Cynthia Pareja 
 Dubin\n\nClass Dates: May 13\, 20\, 27\nTime: 6:30pm-8:30pm\n\nLearn from 
 talented teaching artist Cynthia Pareja Dubin in this three-week course 
 designed to introduce participants to the art of abstract collage. Students 
 will learn how to create dynamic\, expressive compositions using various 
 papers\, materials\, and found objects. They will explore fundamental 
 principles of design\, color theory\, and texture\, encouraging personal 
 expression and creative discovery.\n\nAll materials will be provided. No 
 prior art experience is necessary\, and all skill levels are 
 welcome.\n\nSession 1: May 13\nThe Foundation of Abstract 
 Collage\nIntroduction to abstract art and collage history / Explanation of 
 tools / Materials exploration / Composition basics\n\nSession 2: May 
 20\nInspiration and Narrative\nDeveloping a palette / Layering and texture 
 / Creating a series\n\nSession 3: May 27\nFinalizing and 
 Sharing\nRefinement / Finishing / Group critique and discussion\n\nThis 
 learning program is structured as three distinct\, two-hour sessions\, 
 allowing participants to build on their skills progressively. Participants 
 register for the class with the understanding that they are committing to 
 all three sessions\, to be held on consecutive Wednesday evenings. While 
 unavoidable absences are understood\, the idea is to commit to the full 
 course as the lessons build sequentially. Registration will remain open 
 until May 13\, the date of the initial session.
LOCATION:West Orange - Program Room\, West Orange Public Library
ORGANIZER;CN="West Orange Library":MAILTO:events@westorange.bccls.org
CATEGORIES:
UID:LibCal-10341-16406048
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/16406048
END:VEVENT
